comment: After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that LaVine (MIN) was inside the three point line on his shot attempt was confirmed.
Wiggins (MIN) legally contests Durant's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Towns (MIN) sets the hand-off screen on Waiters (OKC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Dieng (MIN) sets the screen on Waiters (OKC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
L-Slash and LATR show no contact made by Waiters (OKC) to LaVine's (MIN) arm.
LaVine (MIN) makes contact with Durant's (OKC) arm that causes him to lose control of the ball.
Wiggins (MIN) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Durant's (OKC) drive and shot attempt.
Dieng (MIN) and Adams (OKC) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
[Incidental or immaterial] Ibaka (OKC) grabs and pulls Towns's (MIN) jersey affecting his FOM.
LaVine (MIN) commits a take foul on Westbrook (OKC).
Rubio (MIN) commits a take foul on Durant (OKC).
Dieng (MIN) and Towns (MIN) sets the screen on Singler (OKC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Westbrook (OKC) makes incidental contact with Rubio's (MIN) non-shooting arm prior to the start of the upward shooting motion that does not affect his shot attempt.
Ibaka (OKC) and Towns (MIN) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Durant (OKC) and Dieng (MIN) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
LaVine (MIN) commits a take foul on Westbrook (OKC).
